SIMPLE: flatfoot
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: flatfoot
<hw>flat"foot`</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>.
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A foot in which the arch of the instep is
flattened so that the entire sole of the foot rests upon the ground;
also, the deformity, usually congenital, exhibited by such a foot;
splayfoot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flatfoot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: flatfoot
<hw>flat"foot`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a police officer, especially a
foot patrolman.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flat-footed</ent>⟦br⟧
